various roles including as an economist prior to that she worked at the world bank in washington dc from  until  prior public company directorships lundin petroleum ab and sabmiller plc skills and qualifications environmental affairs as director at barrick gold corporation served on the committee that considered and provided oversight on environmental matters finance ten years of experience at goldman sachs and the world bank phd in economics from the university of oxford and mba in finance from the american university audit committee member at barrick gold corporation and seagate technology global business  international affairs traveled to more than  countries over the last decade with a particular focus on the interplay of international business and the global economy while highlighting the key opportunities for investment director of companies with international operations government  regulatory  public policy ten years of experience in the highly regulated banking and financial services industry  mpa in public administration from john f kennedy school of government harvard research  academia author of three new york times bestsellers writing regularly appears in economic and financerelated publications updated april  about — chevroncom skip to main content producing energy responsibly about our success is driven by our people and their commitment to getting results the right way – by operating responsibly executing with excellence applying innovative technologies and capturing new opportunities for profitable growth stories energy stories are unfolding on a global stage find the articles speeches and case studies you care about explore stories the chevron way seven values guide all of our business activities and decisions see what we stand for operational excellence achieving top performance is a stepbystep process and an everyday practice learn our process leadership our board of directors and corporate officers are committed to getting results the right way m