ness and finance news network ms moyo leverages her comprehensive economic understanding to inform a practical investment strategy realise opportunities and manage risks across emerging economies her work examines the interplay between rapidly developing countries international business and the global economy while highlighting investment opportunities and convergence themes publications  winner take all – china’s race for resource and what it means for the world –  new york times bestseller debuting at   as well as entering the wall street journal’s business best sellers at  and the publishers weekly bestseller list at   how the west was lost fifty years of economic folly – and the stark choices that lie ahead – it became a new york times bestseller debuting at  in its first week it also debuted at  in the washington post and  in the wall street journal  dead aid why aid is not working and how there is a better way for africa –  new york times bestseller and is published in chinese english french german greek italian japanese korean polish portuguese and dutch   related speakers nicholas stern leading global economist andy xie renowned economist nouriel roubini renowned economist speaker categories adventure asia banking branding business celebrity china communications corporate social responsibility economics entertainment etiquette europe fitness gen y global affairs hong kong innovation leadership life style management marketing mc media middle east  north africa mena motivational negotiation performance politics productivity sales sports strategy sustainability techonology trends speaker enquiry fill out my online form copyright   by speakers connect all rights reserved home speakers about us clients event photos news faqs contact us stx dambisa f moyo insider trades for seagate technology plc bulletin investor alert tokyo markets close in currencies europe markets london markets expand keep open close expand keep open close expand keep open close expand keep o